-- Morgan Stanley adds advisers from UBS
-- 
-- Thu Nov 11, 2010 4:46pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/11/11/us-morganstanley-idUSTRE6AA5AM20101111

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Morgan Stanley ( MS.N ) Smith Barney has added four financial advisers from UBS ( UBSN.VX ) ( UBS.N ). 

 Benjamin Kusner and Steven Berner joined Morgan Stanley Smith Barney's office in Birmingham, Michigan. William Hanrahan and Shane Meyer joined the company's office in Toledo, Ohio, according to filings with the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority. The four advisers oversaw a combined $184 million of client assets at UBS and generated $1.9 million in annual fees and commissions, according to a source familiar with their business. Hanrahan was an 18-year veteran of UBS and predecessor firm PaineWebber, according to FINRA filings. (Reporting by Helen Kearney; editing by Carol Bishopric)